               <msContents defective="false">
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1" defective="false">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist and of other characters like Gäbrǝʾel (fols. 32ra, 104ra) and St. George (fol. 41ra); names of the owner and the scribe; the word kǝfl “part” (fol. 36rb), another word (addressing the reader) on fol. 28vb; elements of the punctuation signs and of the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
&#xD;
Several groups of lines on the incipit page of Text I (alternating with black lines); two or three initial lines in the incipit of sections (homilies) and subsections (miracles), sometimes alternating with black lines (e.g., fols. 56rb, 86vb, 88va); the first word in the incipit of subsections (hymns), i.e. sälam "salutation"; the word sälam in Text II.</rubric>
